review_blob: copper color, lightly hazy, thin eggshell-white head, no significant lacing. aroma is almost equal parts pine and grapefruit with hints of perspiration and caramel. flavor is primarily grapefruit but with enough caramel maltiness to almost make it seem balanced. nice enough, but the original ruination was near perfection...this version is just really good.

dark brown color, light brown head. mild carbonation. aroma is predominantly still coffee and roasted malts, but with modest notes of blueberry. flavor is tart with coffee and much stronger presence of the blueberry.

medium golden color, clear, very thin white head. aroma has nice grassy and spicy qualities, mildly citrusy as well. flavor initially is lemony, followed by a bit of spice and eases into an earthy/grassy finish. The aroma was quite nice, but the taste wasnt there. not bad though.
hazy, yellowish-golden color. off-white big, frothy head. aroma is funky, musty, tart-like with a lot of fruit. flavor is tart but also sweet. slight bitterness in the finish. quite nice.

medium golden color, thin off-white head. hazy, moderate carbonation. aroma is strong on peach and citrus. flavor is nicely bitter with notes of perspiration, peach and pineapple. flavor is moderately sweet, but is offset nicely by the hops. very nice beer!

deep reddish brown color, light beige head. clear, light to moderate carbonation. aroma is lightly nutty and toasty malts. flavor is slightly nutty with more of a hop presence. slight plasticy quality, not unpleasant. notes of cocoa in the finish.

golden color, clear, light to moderate carbonation. head is white, thin and frothy. aroma is is grassy with notes of nectarine or peach. flavor is nectarine/peach, grassy and little herbal. mouthfeel is fizzy. finish is mildly bitter and nice.
beer_name: New Glarus Moon Man No Coast Pale Ale

review_blob: copper color, thin offwhite head, clear, light carbonation. toasted bready malty notes. body is light to moderate. flavor is dominated by the bready malts. pretty good offering.
hazy golden color, off white head. mild carbonation. aroma is citrusy, peppery, and yeast. flavor is similar profile with a bit of sourness in the aftertaste.

12oz bottle. copper color, almost no head. faint aroma of bready malts and very little else. flavor has some light bready malt flavor, a weird bit of sourness, and a really thin body. frankly, this is quite a disappointment.

12oz bottle. clear golden color with good-sized frothy white head. moderate carbonation. bit of saaz hop spice and cereal in the nose. flavor profile is spicy saaz with a decent amount of floral quality. quite bitter, but still pleasant. decent effort.

12oz bottle, dark brown, decent creamy light brown head. aroma primarily of chocolate with some roasted notes. flavor begins with roasted malt notes, slight hint of alcohol. mild bitterness comes through in the finish and roasty qualities linger for a bit.

22oz bottle, bronze color, hazy, light carbonation. creamy, offwhite head. aroma is heavy on caramel malt, almost buttery. can only pick up a hint of piney hops. flavor is again dominated by a caramel maltiness. flavor has some bitter herbal notes. i assumed when i opened this, itd be hop heavy, but ended up being malt heavy. wonder if this is old.
dark brown color, beige frothy head. slightly nutty aroma, mild hints of toffee. flavor is nutty and the malts are a little more bready. not bad, nothing exciting.

standard gold/yellow color for a pils. clear and lightly carbonated. pretty big frothy head. aroma is nice spicy saaz hops, little bit grassy. flavor is very slight bready malts, not enough saaz in the flavor for my liking, but still not bad. the aroma is pretty nice, but the flavor just doesnt deliver for me.

golden color, big frothy off-white head. aroma is of citrus, grass, bit of pepper, sugar. flavor is light citrus, yeast, grassy hops. hoped for better. for my money saison de pipaix is still the gold standard.

orange/copper color, thick almond colored frothy head. aroma is mild orange and fair bit of spicy hops. flavor is some orange, not as much as expected. much heavier on the hops than expected. finish has a moderate citrusy quality and a little bitter. its different.

12oz can. pale golden color, almost clear, very lightly hazy. head is frothy white, decent at first, quickly diminishing. aroma of wet cardboard, very light spice from the hops. flavor is a bit thin, clean, light spice from the hops, bit more cardboard. actually pleasant in a summer beer kind of manner. could drink this regularly as a thirst quencher.
beer_name: Oskar Blues Mamas Little Yella Pils

review_blob: 12oz bottle. golden, lightly hazy, thin egg-shell white head. aroma is immediately pine, perspiration, minimal citrus (bit of lemon). flavor is piney, lemony, slightly sweet at first and fading quickly, but plenty bitter at the same time. a little grassy and perspiration notes come through in the finish.

beer_brewer_name: Vermont Hard Cider Company, LLC (C&C; Group)
review_blob: very pale color.mine had a good sized fizzy white head. aroma and flavor are both fruity and a bit cloying, but on ice, this is actually a fairly refreshing drink. it has a time and place. after rating I put some crushed blueberries in and had it over ice. even better.
clear, light golden color, moderate sized frothy white head. aroma primarily grassy and floral. moderate bitterness in the flavor, more floral and grassiness. not bad

pint can. lovely deep copper color, with thin beige head. moderate carbonation. first thing that hits me is a strong aroma of pine with hints of perspiration odor (not as bad as it sounds). also a bit of floral hoppiness as well. flavor has plenty of pine with a lot of citrus. mouthfeel is somewhat oily, but still clean. finish is clean, somewhat floral hoppiness, but bitter at the end. totally impressed by this IPA. One of the better Ive had in quite some time.
beer_name: Great River West Coast Style IPA

review_blob: color is mahogany with reddish notes, mostly clear, lightly carbonated. no head to speak of. aroma is caramel, whiskey, dates. flavor is dark fruits, plenty of caramel, butterscotch. not as much whiskey in the flavor as in the aroma. hoppiness is definitely understated. mouthfeel is slightly viscous. quite smooth with some whiskey qualities.

pale gold color, hazy, moderate carbonation. off-white head, not long lasting. aroma has herbal hoppiness, bit floral and spicy. flavor seems a bit too hoppy for the style. lightly sweet, but not a delicate beer.

clear golden color, big, frothy eggshell-white head. moderate to heavy carbonation. nose is heavy on grapefruit and pine with light to moderate caramel maltiness. flavor is piney, grapefruity and resiny with less maltiness. finish is not terribly long

deep orange/light copper color, nice frothy offwhite head. nose has hints of spice and sugar. flavor is lightly spiced, slightly musty. pretty good, but not even in the same class as saison de pipaix.

deep brown color, light brown creamy head. aroma is primarily coffee, little bit of cocoa. bottle reads that cinnamon, pecan, caramel, vanilla and rum are added to this beer. pecan and caramel are noticeable, but the other ingredients my nose doesnt pick up. flavor is similar, coffee, cocoa with pecan and caramel present as well. expected this to be a much thicker beer. really surprised at how thin it is. not necessarily a bad thing.
beer_name: Bent River Jingle Bell Java Stout

review_blob: 12 oz bottle. brownish/amber color, clear. head is minimal and beige. aroma is more pumpkin and much less spice than I anticipated. flavor is a little more allspice and a nice pumpkin balance. pleasantly surprised with this as this style is typically way overspiced for my taste.

12oz bottle. deep dull orange color, hazy to cloudy, head is white and creamy to foamy. sugar and spice in the aroma along with slight notes of citrus. flavor is more spicy, yeast, some citrus. nice beer,

12oz bottle. hazy copper color. thin beige head. aroma has notes of coriander, nutmeg, allspice, and really, very little else. flavor has very subtle hints of sweet potato, but again, is really just completely dominated by the spice. sweet potato is a little more noticeable in the finish and aftertaste.

reddish-brown color, clear, very light carbonation. head is small to medium, light pink/white. aroma is artificial cherry with hints of vanilla. flavor is slightly acidic, slighty tart, but mostly cherry sweet. there is a bit of must and wood in the finish. not too shabby.

clear, light golden, heavily carbonated. frothy white head. nose is slightly bready, with a typical saaz aroma. flavor has abundant spiciness from the saaz, a little bit bitter it would seem for the style, but not unpleasant. a little bit of wet cardboard in the flavor. pleasantly surprised by this.

pinkish red, light pink head, aroma obviously dominated by raspberries, but with a slight maltiness. flavor profile is raspberries, with more of a tartness than i expected. was expecting more of a cloyingly sweet beer. still a decent amount of sweetness, but with plenty of acidity to balance it out. finish is nice and tart and longer than i would have guessed.

clear, pale golden color, white lightly frothy head. light carbonation. aroma is floral with a light grassiness. flavor has a bit of a spice (assuming Saaz are used here), but id a like a bit more "Saazy" character to mine. still nice and refreshing beer.

pale to medium orange color, hazy, head is off-white. aroma is citrusy, a hint of alcohol, sugary malts. flavor is a little citrusy, fairly spicy, with even more alcohol present than in the aroma. not really a fan.

12oz can, medium orange/copper color, almond-colored head, nice and frothy. aroma is indeed loaded with classic west coast hops, grapefruity and moderately caramel. flavor has a similar profile to aroma. quite a well balanced beer.

growler from the brewery. clear, light carbonated, pale orange color. head is egg shell white and thin. nose is mildly citrus and herbal. flavor has a bit of citrus hoppiness. finish was surprisingly longer than I thought it would be with a nice bitterness. havent tried a ton of session IPAs, but this is pretty tasty.

bronze color, off-white head. nose is slight caramel and more noticeable bubblegum from the malt. plenty of spice in the aroma as well. flavor has more caramel than bubblegum from the malts, but there is good amount of bitterness, pine and citrus from the hops. finish is longer than i expected and pleasant. flying dog did well.

pale straw/champagne color, no real head, heavy carbonation. nose is tart apple as youd expect. a little bit artificial. flavor is similar, apple juice thats a bit tart. it is what it is. nothing complex, but quite refreshing on a hot day.
clear, golden, thin white head. aroma of apricots and malt. flavor has plenty of apricot. does have a bit of fruit juice quality to it, but is quite refreshing.
beer_name: Samuel Smiths Organic  Apricot  Fruit Beer

review_blob: Barney died in my glass. Hazy purplish color. initial whitish/purple head. short-lived. hint of alcohol and generic berry fruitiness in the nose. flavor is cloying artificial berry, like a flintstone vitamin. as a serious beer, this cant really be rated, but honestly, there is a refreshing quality to it. would be better on a hot day than a 40-degree april day in iowa.

straw colored, thin head white head. hazy with light carbonation. light notes of lemon in the nose and hints of grass. flavor has notes of coriander, citrus, candied ginger. light floral hoppiness. drinkable enough, but nothing special.

light copper color, clear, light carbonation, off-white head. very little lacing. aroma is mostly citrus with some pine notes and an herbal quality. flavor is light to moderate caramel, with plenty of pine and some grapefruit. hops obviously dominate, but there is enough malt to stand up to it. body is medium and there is a nice long bitter finish. pretty darn good.

color is dark golden. head is eggshell white. heavily carbonated. light notes of citrus, perspiration, with an odd hint of bubblegum. flavor is nice and caramelly, hoppiness is light, floral, mild citrus.
clear, golden color, very fizzy. notes of apple and candied fruit in the nose. flavor is somewhat tart, but sweet also. apples and more candied fruit in the flavor with a clean finish. not bad.

copper color, clear, moderate carbonation, head is almond-colored. nose is citrus with a hint of pine. flavor is moderate caramel, toffee with some decent bitterness the finish has a roasty quality to it. really a well-balanced beer.
cloudy, pale yellow. little citrus in the nose, flavor has notes of sugar, citrus and coriander. not bad.
clear, straw colored, white head, lightly carbonated, aroma is bready malts and grain. flavor is slightly lemony and malty. straightforward and simple, not bad.
very pale gold, hazy, thin white head. nose is light citrus and woody. flavor is flavor is a bit of lemon, some grapefruit and grassy.

clear deep golden, slightly amber. beige super creamy head with good lacing. aroma has lots of caramel, plenty of citrus/pine in the hops, but not overpowering. flavor is a nice balanced mix of caramel malts with plenty of resin/pine/citrus hoppiness. Finish is really long and numbs the tongue a bit. Im totally burned out on DIPAs, but I think this is a really well made one.
